			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Actually I do not think it is illegal to have more than one child in China, but there is a catch.  If a family has one child the State pays for everything; education, medical, college, etcetera - typical socialism thing.  If a family has more than one child, they are then taxed more and the State will not pay for anything for either child.  So it is not that it is illegal to have more than one child, but rather it is near financially impossible to have more than one child.
<br />
I would imagine there is somebody on this board that is recently from China that can shed more light on this.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow this is my stance on abortion:  I think abortions should be legal, but regulated as any other medical practice would be.  The reason, though, why I think they should be legal is because I do not like the idea of the government telling somebody that they <span style="font-style: italic">can not</span> do something.
<br />
That being said, I would not encourage anybody to get an abortion because in most cases I am morally against it.  However, I am open minded and understand that if it is a case of rape, underage teen pregnancy, severe abnormality then that could be acceptable.  The use of abortion as a birth control method is unacceptable.
<br />

<br />
Something that I do not understand is why people are against parental notification for underage girls.  Kids have to have parental notification for a friggin' dental appointment, I think having the parents notified for an abortion procedure is not much to ask for.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
