			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Having been the sperm donor does not give responsibility nor grant rights on a gestating child.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Unless by sperm donor you mean the mother going to the sperm bank for artificial insemination, the mother can bear the child and stick you with child support and other obligations for the next 18 years of your life whether you like it or not.  That, to me, is definitely responsibility.  For that matter it grants rights, too, since you can demand visitation, custody, etc.
<br />

<br />
My point with that is that while yes, it's the woman's body, it's also partly due to the man as well.  And if society is going to make it so that there can be legal consequences to getting a chick pregnant, then the guy should have a say as to whether or not the child is even born.
<br />

<br />
Here's the thing:  people lie.  Condoms break.  Birth control fails.  i.e., accidents happen.  Saying abstinence works every time is a bit silly.  Yes, you <span style="font-style: italic">can</span> just never have sex out of fear that you might get someone pregnant.  However it'd be a lot simpler to just make it so that males have rights regarding the choice to abortion as well.
<br />

<br />
For that matter, let's take it from the other side.  Woman wants an abortion, man doesn't.  Guy can be willing to take sole custody of the child, no child support from the woman, no responsibility after the birth on her part, nothing.  And if she wants to abort the baby there is absolutely nothing the guy can do.  That's not right either.
<br />

<br />
I guess what I'm saying here is that while yes, it's the woman's body, she couldn't have been impregnated without the male half too.  And as such, it's not particularly fair for the male half of the equation to have absolutely no say whatsoever.
<br />

<br />
Flarestar Bladesinger<br />
