<br />

<br />
Explain how genetic tinkering of people who cannot naturally conceive will bring about a substandard child? You need proof before making such a profound statement.
<br />

<br />
Please explain how sterilization will help? Everyone has recessive alleles, some bad (blue eyes, one example). Some genetic defects are autosomal dominant such as Huntington's disorder. Sometimes mutations happen within your sperm or eggs. So now, your children will come out with defects such as Fragile X syndrome. Or, you may work at a nuclear powerplant and you get irradiated, congratulations, you may have had some gene deletion. Viral attacks, ionizing radiation, some harmful chemicals can trigger gene deletion. This can be harmful because a useful dominant allele could be deleted. Right now, you could have mutations that could alter the lives of your potential offspring. Should you be sterilized?
<br />

<br />
I agree with you concerning younger mothers producing healthier children.
<br />

<br />

<br />
In the developed world we live in, survival of the fittest goes out of the window. Until the world population reaches a point where the demand for food exceeds the production of it, nothing will change. What will change the booming population is education. Most of the 3rd world are producing the most children. The reason you may ask, they are not educated on birth control, or what the costs are of having too many children. An educated woman can plan and calculate how many children she can support. This has been proven to work in Mexico City. It can work, we just need to educate people.<br />
